Czech Preparatory Committee Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- A Czech preparatory committee for celebrating the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea was inaugurated with due ceremony in Prague on July 28.
 Attending the ceremony were the general secretary of the Central Committee of the Czechoslovak Communist Party and political and public figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association was elected chairman of the preparatory committee at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee set the days from July 28 to October 12 as a period of celebrations and decided to organize various political and cultural functions, introduce the achievements made by the WPK and the DPRK through media and express solidarity with the Korean people in their just cause in the period.

Repeal of "Taft-Katsura Agreement" Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- More than 10 legislators from the ruling and opposition parties of south Korea including the Uri Party submitted to the "National Assembly" a resolution demanding the United States and Japan declare the repeal of the "Taft-Katsura Agreement" in connection with the lapse of 100 years since its fabrication, according to the south Korean KBS on July 29.
 The resolution said that the "agreement" set the stage for the Japanese imperialists' past domination over Korea and the division of the Korean territory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It denounced the fabrication of the "agreement" by the U.S. and Japan as a criminal breach of international law as it wantonly encroached upon the rights of a sovereign state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded the U.S. and Japan make a formal apology for this and declare the repeal of the "agreement".

Anniversary of Korea's Liberation Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held by the Mongolian Academy of Sciences and a lecture and round-table talks took place in Kinshasa, Democratic Congo, from July 21 to 26 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 Chairman M. Ganjorig and Executive Chairman N. Sarantuya of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development, at the seminar said that for every country and nation to value the Juche character and national identity and give full play to patriotism is a vital issue related to the destiny of the country. They noted that the association would conduct positive activities in diverse forms and ways in the future in Mongolia to learn from the experience of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Otete Gaston Mboyo, chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, in a lecture praised the undying feats President Kim Il Sung performed by defeating Japanese imperialism and bringing about a great event of the liberation of Korea after embarking upon the road of revolution in his teens.
 He noted that the feats of the President are shining more brilliantly thanks to leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jean Baptiste Nkoy, general secretary of the People's Rally for Socialism of Democratic Congo, at the round-table talks referred in detail to the fact that the President led the great anti-Japanese war to victory and after the liberation of Korea he founded the Workers' Party of Korea, the regular armed forces and the state and turned the DPRK into a socialist power, thus laying the foundation for the eternal prosperity and progress of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, seminars, film shows and photo exhibitions took place in Egypt and Libya on July 25 on the occasion of the 52nd anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War and the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the functions were leaders of various political parties, chiefs of organizations, academic figures, members of Juche idea study organizations and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people and people from all walks of life in those countries.

S. Korean Women Students Org. Calls for Celebrating Liberation Day as Day of Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The "National Council of Women Student Representatives" of south Korea reportedly issued a statement titled "Let's celebrate August 15 liberation as August 15 reunification" on July 27.
 The 60th anniversary of August 15 liberation this year can be called a genuine liberation day only when it is celebrated as August 15 reunification, the statement said, stressing that the Koreans should not allow the presence of the U.S. forces in south Korea to go beyond 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization will unite more fellow students so that they might participate in the August 15 grand national festival and arouse stronger fervor for reunification among women throughout south Korea centering on the "Paektu-Halla huge group of women's marchers for reunification". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Calling for holding with splendor the August 15 grand national festival for independence, peace and reunification , the statement underscored the need to successfully stage the festival nationwide so as to celebrate the August 15 liberation as August 15 reunification.

Punishment of GI Criminal Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The 49th candlelight function to honor the memory of woman Kim Myong Ja who was killed by a U.S. military truck was reportedly held at the plaza of Uijongbu Railway Station, Kyonggi Province, on July 29.
 Attending there were members of the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the Democratic Workers' Party and the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions and students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Song Jong Hyon, permanent representative of the All-Citizens Measure Committee for the Solution of the Issue of the U.S. Military Base in the Northern District of Kyonggi Province, said this land does not protect the people, calling upon people from all walks of life to punish the GI criminal and retake the lost independence of the nation by their own efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Hong Gu, representative of the Emergency Measure Committee for Probing the Truth about the Murder Case by a U.S. Military Truck, called upon the people to bring the killer to justice and fight it out till he is punished. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants shouted "End to all the GIs' crimes in this land", holding candlelights.

Fresh Water Fish Breeding Encouraged in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- Breeding of fresh water fish is encouraged throughout the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Fish farms and spawning ponds under the Pyongyang City Fish Farm Management Bureau have released 80 million fry of fish including carp and gibel in rivers and reservoirs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sonnae Youth Fish Farm has secured fish fry 6 times those in the previous year and built a new facility with a capacity to hatch millions of fish spawn. 
 The Sariwon City Fish Farm is breeding various kinds of fish stage by stage by cultivating microbes with excrements of domestic animals and grass to suit the ecological features of fresh water fish. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has secured breeding fish and raised them in a scientific and technical way to provide over 7.5 million fry to fish farms of several units and release millions in rivers and streams. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also introduced an advanced method of collecting and hatching fish spawn, with the result that it has raised the incubation rate up to 90 percent and produced several million fry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fish farm where Choe Jung Hwa works as manager is breeding various kinds of fish in a scientific and intensive way. It has secured enough fry of fish including carp and catfish and bred catfish by forming shoals and regulating nutrition, light and water temperature in a scientific and technical way to suit their ecological features.
 The farm has also increased the production of fat fish with a method of cultivating triploid catfish by hydrostatic pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Catfish farms in Pyongyang and other parts of the country are using a newly-developed assorted feed to raise the weight increasing rate of catfish fry.

Coastal Environment Improved in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The coastal environment of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, a maritime nation, has been bettered as the days go by.
 The government has directed many efforts to providing a clean environment to the people, thus creating beautiful coastal scenery and better environment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The country has such institutional mechanisms as the Law on Forestry, Law on Fishery, Law on Water Resources and Law on Preventing Sea Pollution.
 It has more than a thousand nature-protection reserves such as natural, plant, animal and aquatic resources reserves. Among them are over 60 sea reserves including the Ongjin aquatic resources reserve and the West Sea Barrage natural park.
 The sizes of coastal residential quarters including Wonsan, Hamhung, Haeju and Nampho have been set properly and coastal towns have dispersed on a small or medium scale to protect well coastal environment and the water quality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of sanatoriums and rest homes have been built on the east coast including Sinpho, Majon, Sokhu, Hongwon, Kyongpho and Mt. Chilbo as the transparency of water there is 8-10 meters and chemical oxygen demand and biochemical oxygen demand are 3 milligrams per a liter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the coastal economic development such as building of industrial establishments and ports and reclamation of tideland, the primary attention has been directed to their influence on environment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, a new perspective blueprint for land development has been drawn up in 2004 and it is being implemented on a full scale, thus laying a foundation to provide a better coastal environment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An intensive campaign for preserving and managing the coastal environment has been conducted in each period of the general mobilization for land construction. This year a vast acreage of wind break belt with halo-tolerant plants has been created in the west coastal areas including Onchon County, South Phyongan Province, and Yomju County, North Phyongan Province, and a several-hundred-meter-long breakwater built in Sinpho City, South Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the establishment of a well-organized system for observing the coasts and territorial waters of the country, coastal environment and pollution are under regular observation and necessary steps taken.

Kim Jong Il Inspects Command of Large Combined Unit of KPA and Its Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected the command of the large combined unit and Unit 615 honored with the title of   Kum Song Lifeguard of the KPA situated in the forefront area in the central sector of the front.
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greeted on the spot by the commanding officers of the large combined unit.
 He was briefed on the performance of the unit's duty by the commander of the unit.
 Expressing satisfaction over the fact that the officers and men of the unit have thoroughly implemented the military line of the WPK, thus consolidating the military bulwark of Korean style socialism as firm as a rock, he set forth the highly important tasks which would serve as guidelines in further increasing the militancy of the unit and turning the defence theatre into an invulnerable fortress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After inspecting the command, he enjoyed a performance given by the art squad of the large combined unit at the servicemen's hall together with the officers and men of the unit and their families. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He then inspected KPA Unit 615 honored with the title of Kum Song Lifeguard.
 After being saluted, he went round the room dedicated to the history of the unit, conducted by its commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the exploits performed by the unit honored with the field guidance given by President Kim Il Sung several times. The meritorious unit has displayed matchless patriotic devotion and popular heroism for the Party and the leader, the country and the people up to this date since the days of the hard-fought Fatherland Liberation War, performing distinguished feats in the war and in the struggle to defend the forefront of socialism and producing at least 30 heroes of the Republic including 16 heroes of Phohang and many recipients of state orders, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at the operation study room to learn in detail with the training of the commanding officers of the unit. There he set forth tasks to be fulfilled to increase the unit's combat capability in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the servicemen's hall and other entertainment facilities and logistic facilities, he got familiar with the political and ideological education and the management of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with soldiers Kim Sin Hyok and Kim Sin Il, twin brothers, who went to the forefront from Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he moved on to the duck farm built by the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He put forward the tasks to be fulfilled to boost the duck production, saying that the farm should operate at its fullest capacity to pay off profusely. 
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit.
